PSXDataSelector.nativeStatement: SELECT DISTINCT CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPEID, CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPENAME FROM CONTENTTYPES, RXSLOTCONTENT WHERE CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPEID = RXSLOTCONTENT.CONTENTTYPEID AND RXSLOTCONTENT.SLOTID = :"PSXSingleParam/sys_slotid" ORDER BY CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPENAME ASC

SELECT DISTINCT PSX_TEMPLATE.STYLESHEETNAME,PSX_TEMPLATE.TEMPLATE_ID, PSX_TEMPLATE.ASSEMBLYURL, PSX_TEMPLATE.NAME, PSX_TEMPLATE.LABEL FROM PSX_TEMPLATE, RXVARIANTSLOTTYPE, CONTENTSTATUS, PSX_CONTENTTYPE_TEMPLATE CTT WHERE CONTENTSTATUS.CONTENTTYPEID = CTT.CONTENTTYPEID AND CTT.TEMPLATE_ID = PSX_TEMPLATE.TEMPLATE_ID AND CONTENTSTATUS.CONTENTID = :"PSXSingleParam/sys_contentid" AND (PSX_TEMPLATE.AATYPE<>2 OR PSX_TEMPLATE.AATYPE IS NULL) ORDER BY PSX_TEMPLATE.NAME ASC

PSXDataSet.name: contentstatus
PSXDataSet.description: This resource is used in the cache handler. All it returns so far is the current revision for the supplied contentId.

PSXDataSet.name: relatedcontentitemset
PSXDataSet.description: This resource returns all related content items currently available. Its used to initialize the PSContentItemDependencyTree for caching.

PSXDataSelector.nativeStatement: SELECT DISTINCT PSX_TEMPLATE.STYLESHEETNAME,PSX_TEMPLATE.TEMPLATE_ID, PSX_TEMPLATE.ASSEMBLYURL, PSX_TEMPLATE.NAME, PSX_TEMPLATE.LABEL FROM PSX_TEMPLATE, RXVARIANTSLOTTYPE, CONTENTSTATUS, RXVARIANTCOMMUNITY, PSX_CONTENTTYPE_TEMPLATE CTT WHERE CONTENTSTATUS.CONTENTTYPEID = CTT.CONTENTTYPEID AND CTT.TEMPLATE_ID = PSX_TEMPLATE.TEMPLATE_ID AND PSX_TEMPLATE.TEMPLATE_ID = RXVARIANTCOMMUNITY.VARIANTID AND RXVARIANTCOMMUNITY.COMMUNITYID = :"PSXUserContext/User/SessionObject/sys_community" AND CONTENTSTATUS.CONTENTID = :"PSXSingleParam/sys_contentid" AND (PSX_TEMPLATE.AATYPE<>2 OR PSX_TEMPLATE.AATYPE IS NULL) ORDER BY PSX_TEMPLATE.NAME ASC

PSXDataSet.name: Dataset13886
PSXDataSet.description: Dummy update resource. All work is done in the pre-exit sys_casModifyRelatedContent. This is kept here because we don't want to change the active assembly user interface.
